snippet.textDisplay: The helicopter they were flying in is infact blue and white. You can enter the tail number on flightaware and see the last flight details and info on the helicopter. To me, that pilot had no business descending at that rate especially turning near a closed mountain. I just wish the pilot declared an emergency and told ATC we need to make an emergency landing before he got all the way out there. So many variables. I wish ATC landed them quicker and didn’t have them going off of visuals and not instrumentals, especially on such a foggy day. I feel like they failed them in some ways. Though it’s up to the pilot if they think it’s safe to fly and can handle it and I personally think he had no right taking them up there that morning. The fog was so dense like a thick blanket over the city. We aren’t used to that fog here maybe he underestimated how bad it was. Rest in peace to the lives lost. Tragic.
